{{unreferenced|date= January 2012}}
The '''Canadian Private Copying Collective''' is a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[non-profit]]/[[non-government organization]] created in 1999 to collect and distribute private copying [[royalties]]. The organization represents [[songwriters]], [[recording artists]], [[Music publisher (popular music)|music publisher]]s and [[recording company|recording companies]]. Issues are brought before the [[Copyright Board of Canada]].

